commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor all occurrences of Person into Task
commitResults.messageBody:
The abstraction of a Person should be changed to a Task because the project is a planner now.

Let's rename the Person class and package, any PERSON constant and any person occurrence.

The abstraction of the Name field should be changed to Title because it
is clearer as the title of a Task.

Let's rename the Name class, constants and its occurrences.

Let's give placeholders to those fields in the add command, implemented
in the AddCommandParser class.

TextField used only allows a single line which can be inconvenient for
writing tasks and descriptions.

add line breaks in command input.

enter with shift+enter to introduce line breaks.

Optional fields of task are still rendered on the view and
would be better to appear dynamically for aesthetic
purposes. Details of a task are rendered statically in the
taskListCard fxml and should become dynamic.

Let's refactor details of the task into its own class that
is responsible for controlling the display of each task field.

Fix bug: recurringSchedule not added to taskCard
Refactor rendering of taskfields onto view, enable assert
commitResults.messageBody:
Each of the task fields in the taskCardDetails have individual
methods and have a lot of duplicate code.

Using a command-like pattern can be more easily extensible
for the rendering of each field. It also maintains the
responsibility of knowing the values of each field within
Task.

Let's use Task to return the compulsory and optional fields
and their values to the TaskCardDetails and render them
according to these 2 variables instead of by fields.

commitResults.messageBody:
Each Task object needs their own set of Tag objects and they
might not be unique. It would be more Object-Oriented to
allow a Task consist of some Tags that are shared among all
the Tasks, as this allows Tag to be a separate entity without
needing to be instantiated for a Task.

Let's create a UniqueTagList under Planner that exposes an
observableList for Ui to watch, and update this
UniqueTagList whenever there is a change.

commitResults.messageBody:
Viewing date only filters the list but not show the date on
the calendar when the calendar is so prominent.

Linking the viewing date to the calendar view will be more
intuitive and convenient for the user.

Let's make an observable calendar date which allows the
calendar panel to receive updates from the view day
command, and update the calendar view accordingly.

commitResults.messageBody:
Tag panel uses ListView whose slider resizes according to
the elements it contains. This causes a glitchy resizing issue
when the elements sizes are too different. This is a known
bug of JavaFX and has no clear solution.

The issue can be solved by hiding the slider such that users
cannot access the issue at all.
